<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF81EF42FF42FF23FDFBFEDC" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF81EF42FF42FF23FC9CFEA5" blockId="41.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FF42FF23FEE7FF08" bold="true" box="[199,338,150,176]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Comments:</emphasis>
The collected specimens were tentatively assigned to this species, as they also present features that could be interpreted as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF81EF42FDB7FF0FFD6FFF6C" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[562,730,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phaneropterini">Phaneropterini</taxonomicName>
, specifically species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF81EF42FB25FF0FFA2DFF6C" authority="Piza, 1960" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1960" box="[1184,1432,186,212]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mendesius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FB25FF0FFAADFF6C" box="[1184,1304,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Mendesius</emphasis>
Piza, 1960
</taxonomicName>
. An extensive revision of the species of both genera, and also of the relations among genera and tribes are necessary, including 
<typeStatus id="827FB2C9FF81EF42FE8DFEB7FEDAFEA4" box="[264,367,258,284]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation particularly for 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF81EF42FD28FEB6FC97FEA4" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1907" box="[685,802,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Hyperphrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF81EF42FD28FEB6FC97FEA4" box="[685,802,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. signata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
